parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine overheating in stop-and-go traffic can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or even lead to engine damage, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The temperature gauge goes into the red zone
coolant is dispersed from the cooling system overflow

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire cupping and premature wear can cause poor handling, vibration, and wobbling, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Cupping or uneven wear on the tire
wobbling or shaking of the front end

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire separation and blowouts can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially fatal injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tire Out of Round and Radial Runout
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire out of round and radial runout can cause vibration, wobbling, and poor handling, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: wobbling or shaking of the front end.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Air Leaks and Tire Pressure Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Air leaks and tire pressure issues can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially fatal injuries.
symptoms: wobbling or shaking of the front end.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Speed wobbles and handling issues can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially fatal injuries.
symptoms: wobbling or shaking of the front end.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rear brake lockup and shuttering can cause the motorcycle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when traveling at low speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: the motorcycle pulls to one side
and the motorcycle becomes difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The overheating of the brakes and coolant leaks can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially in heavy traffic or stop-and-go conditions.
symptoms: coolant leaks onto the brakes and rear tire
the brakes become slippery and uncontrollable
and steam rises from the brakes and rear wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The constant squealing of the brakes and the front calipers hanging up and dragging on the rotors can cause the brakes to overheat and fail, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: the front calipers hang up and drag on the rotors
and the brakes feel spongy or soft.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine and clutch can cause the motorcycle to lose power and control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: the clutch plate clip and ring seal fail
and the motorcycle loses power and control.
